full_summary:
### Tender Announcement: Programmer/Analyst (Senior), Web Designer (Senior), and Database Administrator (Intermediate)

#### Issuing Authority
Department of National Defence

#### Procurement Reference Number
W3999-22-CE01

#### Tender Closing Date
Thursday, January 5th, 2023, at 14:00:00

#### Contact Information
* Name: Yves Auger
* Email: DapServicesBidReceiving-DoaServicesReceptionDesSoumissions@forces.gc.ca
* Phone: (204) 833-2500 x5246

#### Overview
The Department of National Defence (DND) is seeking a contract for the provision of Programmer/Analyst (Senior), Web Designer (Senior), and Database Administrator (Intermediate) services. This requirement is part of the Task-Based Informatics Professional Services (TBIPS) Supply Arrangement.

#### Services Required
* Programmer/Analyst (Senior): 235 days
* Web Designer (Senior): 235 days
* Database Administrator (Intermediate): 10 days

#### Security Clearance
The successful bidder will require a Secret level security clearance.

#### Location
The services will be performed in Manitoba, with specific locations to be determined.

#### Payment Terms
The contractual payment terms will be as per the standard government payment terms.

#### Tender Documents
The tender documents will be provided to pre-qualified suppliers under the TBIPS Supply Arrangement. Interested bidders must confirm their interest with Yves Auger at DapServicesBidReceiving-DoaServicesReceptionDesSoumissions@forces.gc.ca by [date].

#### Pre-Qualification
Suppliers must be pre-qualified under the TBIPS Supply Arrangement to participate in this opportunity. For more information, please contact Public Works and Government Services Canada (PWGSC) at RCNMDAI.-NCRIMOS@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca.

#### Governing Law
This procurement is subject to the laws of the Province of Manitoba.

#### Language of Communication
Both English and French are accepted languages for communication.

#### Contract Period
The contract period will be for one (1) year, with four (4) irrevocable option years.

#### Evaluation Criteria
The evaluation criteria will be based on the following aspects:
* Technical submitted solutions.
* Price.
* Other criteria as specified in the tender package.

#### Tender Submission
Tenders must be submitted electronically, in the format specified in the tender package, by the deadline. Late submissions will not
